2012 Stanley Cup playoffs: Capitals-Bruins series predictably gets chippy
View Photo Gallery — 2012 Stanley Cup playoffs: Bruins edge Capitals for 2-1 series lead. By John Feinstein, It was Brooks Laich who pointed out late Monday night that one never knows when a Stanley Cup playoff series will turn chippy — or worse — but that it is almost inevitable. “Sometimes it happens right away in the first game, sometimes it takes two or three games,” he said in the quiet of a losing locker room. “Things start to happen. They’re trying to get you off your game, you’re trying to get them off theirs.”
The Capitals forward smiled briefly. “There’s a lot of verbal jousting going on out there.”
